63.1	The_Edge	The Edge	David Howell Evans (born 8 August 1961), more widely known by his stage name The Edge (or just Edge), is a musician best known as the guitarist, backing vocalist, and keyboardist of the Irish rock band U2. A member of the group since its inception, he has recorded 12 studio albums with the band and has released one solo record. As a guitarist, The Edge has crafted a minimalistic and textural style of playing. His use of a rhythmic delay effect yields a distinctive ambient, chiming sound that has become a signature of U2's music.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/The_Edge_360_Tour_Foxboro_2009.jpg/220px-The_Edge_360_Tour_Foxboro_2009.jpg
